title: Georgia Garnett
text:
Georgia Garnett (born 5 September 2001) is an <a href="Australian%20rules%20football">Australian rules football</a>er who plays for <a href="Greater%20Western%20Sydney%20Giants%23AFL%20Women%27s%20team">Greater Western Sydney</a> in the <a href="AFL%20Women%27s">AFL Women's</a> (AFLW).
AFLW career.
Garnett was drafted by <a href="Greater%20Western%20Sydney%20Giants%23AFL%20Women%27s%20team">Greater Western Sydney</a> in the <a href="2019%20AFL%20Women%27s%20draft">2019 AFL Women's draft</a> with the 90th pick. After not playing in the <a href="2020%20AFL%20Women%27s%20season">2020 season</a>, Garnett made her debut in the <a href="2021%20AFL%20Women%27s%20season">2021 season</a> against <a href="Gold%20Coast%20Suns%23AFL%20Women%27s%20team">Gold Coast</a>. Finishing the season with seven appearances, she was selected for the 2021 <a href="22%20Under%2022%20team">22under22 team</a>.
